rComments: Really interesting lectures, very engaging and definitely passionate about what he does but the content is way too niche for an intro course. If you're intro environmental studies and art this is great but for the average art history student it's almost painfully dull. Important to read ALL the assigned readings for the exam and go to class!

rComments: I found Cheetham's lectures dull. I frequently skipped lecture to stay home - might as well sleep in my own bed than the lecture hall. He is very passionate about his material, however the Anthropocene is a niche subject of study & therefore difficult to engage in. He also assigns copious amounts of DRY readings, which are difficult to get through.

rComments: if you're looking to study real art history, his class may not be for you. his course content seems to be out of agricultural and urban studies, so lots of photos of farms and pictures of dog-walking signs
he likes to start on time (ten minutes early) so make sure you don't arrive late (that is, on time) or you'll be spending a lot of time in the hallway

Public Art in Toronto is the best class because you get to tour the city and take a breather in between classes. Prof Mark makes lectures engaging and he replies emails like texts! Don't be afraid to ask him for help anytime.

Prof Cheetham is a really nice guy and seems to care a lot about his course, "Public Art in Toronto". However he isn't very interesting and he pretty much makes an already boring class even less interesting. He's a good guy though and is a very fair marker and teacher.
Very interesting course.

Public Art in Toronto is exactly how you'd imagine it: walking around the city looking at public displays of art. Though there is no final exam there is a seminar and 8 page research essay on topics of your choosing that shouldn't be taken lightly.  Overall this was one of the best and most interesting courses I've ever taken!
His lectures are insightful. Really heavy reading even for an art history class. Exams questions: WHAAAAT

Great class, terrific content.  However, the multiple choice tests are not a fair evaluation tool - too few questions and too many trick questions. Your grade will not reflect what you have learned - unless you're lucky.
Really enthusiastic. He's an expert and it shows! I enjoyed his lectures very much and I learned a lot. I would definitely take more offerings from Dr. Cheetham. Crazy hair.

Cheetham's lectures were reasonably enjoyable but my expectations for this class were incredibly high & consequentially let down. lectures were interesting, not necessarily useful. readings extreme, tests were overly vague. majorly disappointed we were given all of 3/4 (BLAND) topics for the essay when it could have been such an exciting assignment

Even though my interest in the course material was low, I enjoyed every minute of his lectures simply because I loved listening to him. He was enthusiastic, engaging, funny, fun and not at all pretentious. I would have to agree with everyone about his tests though... what were they even about??
Awesome!!!! Innovative, ground-breaking, up-to-April2006-current.  Interesting, humourous, and nice to look at.  Incredible speaker.
